# Internal plans, prompts and working notes.
# netlify.toml sets publish = "." — every tracked file at the repo root is deployed and
# publicly fetchable. /company-profile.md (67 KB of confidential business analysis) and
# /promptseo.md were both live and returning HTTP 200. Keep these files local: if you need
# one deployed, move it under src/pages and route it deliberately.
# Patterns are anchored with a leading "/" so they only ever match the repo root. Without
# it, git applies them at every level and a future public/images/ca-hero.png or
# docs/prompt.md would be silently untracked.
/image-prompts-for-blogs.md
/blogsystem.md
/blogsgenerateprompt.md
/cityprompt.md
/cityprompt2.md
/company-profile.md
/countryprompt.md
/kolkatacomplexesandsociety.md
/newpage.md
/newpageofcourse.md
/newpages2.md
/newuniquepages.md
/page404error.md
/pagenotfound.md
/planbyclaude.md
/prompt.md
/prompt1.md
/promptcertificate.md
/promptseo.md
/schoolnames.md
/statespagesplan.md
/uiuxplan.md
/VISIBILITY-100X-MASTER-PLAN.md
/VISIBILITY-SEO-AEO-PLAN.md

# Debug screenshots taken while building pages: root-level scratch, never referenced by the
# site, but they were deploying as public assets. Real page images live in public/images/
# and content/, which these patterns deliberately do not reach.
/ca-*.png
/de-*.png
/dps-*.png
/germany-*.png
/heritage-*.png
/donbosco-*.png
/qa-*.png
/sa-*.png
/*-1280*.png
/*-390*.png
/*-1280*.jpeg
/*-390*.jpeg
/bash.exe.stackdump
/et --hard HEAD

